The paper deals with the comparison of the expressive power of different process calculi, specifically the synchronous and asynchronous $\pi$-calculi. This falls under the area of formal methods and theoretical computer science, which is covered by several sub-categories on arXiv. 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal methods and process calculi, which are closely related to logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper deals with the comparison of different process calculi, which are used to model and reason about concurrent and distributed systems. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with distributed systems and the comparison of different process calculi in terms of their expressive power. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with formal models of computation and their expressive power. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the comparison of different process calculi, which are used in software engineering to model and reason about concurrent and distributed systems.
